From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] gatt-database: make GATT LE-only (drop BR/EDR ATT + SDP)

Bridgething turns the Car Thing into a Bluetooth peripheral that a phone
talks to over BR/EDR (RFCOMM: iAP2 for iOS, the bridgething SPP for
Android) and, separately, over LE: the device is a GATT client of the
phone's LE services and hosts a small LE pair-trigger GATT service.
Nothing in the product consumes GATT over the classic BR/EDR transport.

Stock BlueZ unconditionally publishes the Generic Access, Generic
Attribute, and Device Information SDP records carrying an ATT/L2CAP
PSM-31 protocol descriptor, and listens for ATT on BR/EDR L2CAP PSM 31.
To a dual-mode central this advertises "GATT is reachable over BR/EDR",
so it bridges an ATT channel onto the existing classic ACL and uses that
for GATT instead of opening an LE connection. On this product that
bearer is a dead end: the LE-only services the device needs (media
volume, notifications) are never served over it, the writes that request
them time out, and the failed ATT transaction tears the whole device
object down, dragging the classic link with it.

Make GATT strictly LE-only: suppress all GATT SDP record publication
(database_add_record becomes a no-op) and remove the BR/EDR ATT PSM-31
listener. The LE ATT listener (fixed CID 4), the in-memory GATT
database, and every LE GATT client/server path are untouched, so LE
discovery and the device's own pair-trigger service keep working. EATT's
BR/EDR PSM is already gated off by the default single-channel build.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [product-specific use case]
---

diff --git a/src/gatt-database.c b/src/gatt-database.c
--- a/src/gatt-database.c
+++ b/src/gatt-database.c
@@ -823,6 +823,15 @@
 	const char *name = NULL;
 	char uuidstr[MAX_LEN_UUID_STR];

+	/* Superbird: no GATT-over-BR/EDR. This product uses BR/EDR only for
+	 * RFCOMM (iAP2 + the bridgething SPP) and has no GATT-over-BR/EDR
+	 * consumer. Publishing GAP/GATT/DIS SDP records advertises GATT
+	 * reachability over the classic ATT bearer, which steers dual-mode
+	 * central peers onto BR/EDR ATT instead of opening LE. Suppress all
+	 * GATT SDP record publication so GATT stays LE-only.
+	 */
+	return;
+
 	gatt_db_attribute_get_service_uuid(attr, &uuid);

 	switch (uuid.type) {
@@ -4094,20 +4103,10 @@
 	}

 bredr:
-	/* BR/EDR socket */
-	if (btd_adapter_get_bredr(adapter)) {
-		database->bredr_io = bt_io_listen(connect_cb, NULL, NULL, NULL,
-					&gerr, BT_IO_OPT_SOURCE_BDADDR, addr,
-					BT_IO_OPT_PSM, BT_ATT_PSM,
-					BT_IO_OPT_SEC_LEVEL, BT_IO_SEC_MEDIUM,
-					BT_IO_OPT_MTU, btd_opts.gatt_mtu,
-					BT_IO_OPT_INVALID);
-		if (database->bredr_io == NULL) {
-			error("Failed to start listening: %s", gerr->message);
-			g_error_free(gerr);
-			goto fail;
-		}
-	}
+	/* Superbird: BR/EDR ATT (L2CAP PSM 31) listener removed; GATT is
+	 * LE-only (see database_add_record). The bredr: label is kept as the
+	 * goto target from the gatt_channels == 1 single-channel path above.
+	 */

 	if (g_dbus_register_interface(btd_get_dbus_connection(),
 						adapter_get_path(adapter),
